ZH: 我们应允他们的请求。
EN: We agreed to their request.

ZH: 他毫不犹豫地应允了我的邀请。
EN: He readily agreed to my invitation without hesitation.

ZH: 只要你答应，我就会应允的。
EN: I will agree as long as you promise.

ZH: 他不愿意应允我的建议。
EN: He is unwilling to comply with my suggestion.

ZH: 我已经应允了你的请求，现在轮到你履行承诺了。
EN: I have already consented to your request, now it's your turn to fulfill your promise.

ZH: 在我父母的坚决要求下，我最终应允了回家过年。
EN: Under my parents' insistence, I finally agreed to go home for the New Year.

ZH: 他的请求太过分了，我无法应允。
EN: His request was too extreme, I cannot grant it.

ZH: 考虑到现实条件，我们不能应允他的要求。
EN: Considering the practical circumstances, we cannot comply with his demands.

ZH: 我们非常高兴地接受了他的应允。
EN: We happily accepted his agreement.

ZH: 我会考虑并尽快给您一个应允。
EN: I will consider and give you a response as soon as possible.

ZH: 他终于应允参加了我们的会议。
EN: He finally agreed to attend our meeting.

ZH: 作为回报，他应允帮助我完成项目。
EN: As a favor, he agreed to assist me in completing the project.

ZH: 只有在你答应老师的要求后，她才会应允你去外出。
EN: She will only grant your permission to go out after you agree to the teacher's requirements.

ZH: 他不愿意应允妻子的要求。
EN: He is unwilling to comply with his wife's demands.

ZH: 我提出了一项建议，但没有人应允。
EN: I made a suggestion, but nobody agreed.

ZH: 我们希望您能应允我们的要求。
EN: We hope you can grant our request.

ZH: 我们需要你的应允来实施这项计划。
EN: We require your agreement to proceed with this plan.

ZH: 如果你答应我，我会应允你的请求。
EN: If you agree with me, I will grant your request.

ZH: 我被要求应允一项困难的任务。
EN: I have been asked to accept a challenging task.

ZH: 她迟疑了一下，然后应允了我的请求。
EN: She hesitated for a moment and then agreed to my request.
